commitResults.messageTitle: Rename Bot. Added Greet and Exit messages.
Added List, Add To List functionality
commitResults.messageBody:
- Refactored print method in Chatbot.java to accept String arrays
- Created Task.java to represent each user created task

- Created InputHandler.java to separate input handling from Blu.java
- Operations on list moved to TaskList.java
- Added toString method for Task to print out task's title
- Change getTask in TaskList.java to use 1-based indexing

commitResults.messageTitle: Added tracking of three subtypes of tasks
commitResults.messageBody:
- Refactored InputHandler to use switch/case statements
- Added method to retrieve number of tasks in TaskList.java
- Change addTask method in Chatbot.java to accept Task object instead

- Fixed bug in InputHandler.java where first word of deadline/event
  description was not included
- Created BluException class and three exception subclasses
  - IllegalCommand used when there are missing parameters
  - InvalidCommand used for commands that are not supported
  - IllegalParameter used when parameter does not satisfy given
    constraints
- runtest.sh now complies all java files in subdirectories

- Refactored InputHandler to call a method to validate number of command
  parameters

commitResults.messageBody:
Previously storage and tasklist exceptions in each command
were handled in each Command subclass.

Storage and tasklist exceptions are now handled in their
respective .java file

Fix bug in UnmarkCommand.java where unmark command
was not correctly unmarking the task given

Fix bug in InputParser.java where switch statement
was not returning DeleteCommand class

Add J-Unit tests for TaskDecoder.java and TaskList.java

Fixed a bug in TaskDecoder where "==" operator was used instead
of ".equals()" for comparing strings

commitResults.messageTitle: Fixed bug where welcome message is not displayed
commitResults.messageBody:
Upon startup, Blu does not display welcome message as expected.
This is because the method to display the welcome message is
never called in the application.

Create the welcome message in init() and displays it in start().
Change welcome message to include canonical path of the storage
file instead.

This allows users to locate the file path easily.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add assertions to non-empty command and file write
commitResults.messageBody:
Program assumes command parse by input parser is always a
non-null value. It also assumes that the tasks will be
successfully saved to the file.

This can lead to unintended bugs caused by the developer,
as both cases are not supposed to be empty under any
circumstances.

Use assert statements to indicate a possible bug within
these two cases, which violates the assumption that both
commands and file write operations should be non-empty.

This is allow runtime to detect any bugs made by the developer,
allowing the program to terminate earlier safely.
